<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 01:55:43 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>科学家通过阻断单个阿尔茨海默病蛋白来恢复记忆</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/scientists-restore-memory-by-blocking-a-single-alzheimers-protein</link><description>研究人员发现了一种对抗阿尔茨海默病的新潜在武器：阻断一种名为 PTP1B 的蛋白质。在小鼠中，这种方法可以增强记忆力并帮助大脑免疫细胞清除有害的斑块积聚。由于 PTP1B 还与糖尿病和肥胖（这两种阿尔茨海默病的危险因素）有关，因此它可以提供更广泛的治疗策略。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-restore-memory-by-blocking-a-single-alzheimers-protein2.webp" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 01:55:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/scientists-restore-memory-by-blocking-a-single-alzheimers-protein</guid></item><item><title>健康猴和帕金森猴外苍白球神经元尖峰活动的时间变异性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/temporal-variability-in-the-spiking-activity-of-neurons-in-the-external-globus-pallidus-in-healthy-and-parkinsonian-monkeys</link><description>第一份关于清醒猴子苍白球外段（GPe）体内细胞外记录的报告描述，大多数 GPe 神经元表现出高频尖峰活动，并伴有间歇（高频放电与暂停，HFD-P），而较小比例据说表现出低频放电与突发（LFD-B； &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/temporal-variability-in-the-spiking-activity-of-neurons-in-the-external-globus-pallidus-in-healthy-and-parkinsonian-monkeys.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 01:40:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/temporal-variability-in-the-spiking-activity-of-neurons-in-the-external-globus-pallidus-in-healthy-and-parkinsonian-monkeys</guid></item><item><title>Android 展会：I/O 版 |双子座智能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-android-show-i-o-edition-gemini-intelligence</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 01:25:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-android-show-i-o-edition-gemini-intelligence</guid></item><item><title>科学家称认知能力下降并非不可避免——你的大脑在任何年龄段都可以改善</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/scientists-say-cognitive-decline-isnt-inevitable-your-brain-can-improve-at-any-age</link><description>一项长期研究发现，无论年龄大小，通过一致的日常习惯、认知训练和个性化支持，大脑健康可以在一生中得到改善。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-say-cognitive-decline-isnt-inevitable-your-brain-can-improve-at-any-age.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 01:10:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/scientists-say-cognitive-decline-isnt-inevitable-your-brain-can-improve-at-any-age</guid></item><item><title>新型抗体修复急性脊髓损伤</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/novel-antibody-repairs-acute-spinal-cord-lesions</link><description>一项多国临床试验表明，抗 Nogo-A 抗体 NG101 可加速脊髓损伤愈合并促进神经组织再生。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/novel-antibody-repairs-acute-spinal-cord-lesions.jpg" /&gt; 由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 00:55:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/novel-antibody-repairs-acute-spinal-cord-lesions</guid></item><item><title>引力波可能会在冷原子发出的光中留下痕迹</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/gravitational-waves-could-leave-traces-in-light-from-cold-atoms</link><description>新的理论工作表明，原子发射的光模式可用于探测传统探测器范围之外频率的引力波&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/gravitational-waves-could-leave-traces-in-light-from-cold-atoms.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 00:40:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/gravitational-waves-could-leave-traces-in-light-from-cold-atoms</guid></item><item><title>情报的商品化：为什么人工智能聚合器将击败基础模型</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-commoditization-of-intelligence-why-ai-aggregators-will-beat-foundation-models</link><description>目前，每个人都在观看主要科技巨头在人工智能军备竞赛中投入数十亿美元，为本周出现在排行榜上的基础模型欢呼。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-commoditization-of-intelligence-why-ai-aggregators-will-beat-foundation-models.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 00:25:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-commoditization-of-intelligence-why-ai-aggregators-will-beat-foundation-models</guid></item><item><title>肺部如何通过调整对更深层次威胁的反应来平衡防御和损伤</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/how-lungs-balance-defense-and-damage-by-tuning-responses-to-deeper-threats</link><description>形成身体与外部环境之间边界的屏障器官，如肺、皮肤和肠道，面临着艰难的平衡行为。他们必须对感染等威胁做出快速反应，但也需要避免引发不必要的炎症，从而损害组织。由怀特海研究所成员 Pulin Li 和她实验室的研究生 Diep Nguyen 领导的一项新研究揭示了肺部管理这种权衡的一种方式。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-lungs-balance-defense-and-damage-by-tuning-responses-to-deeper-threats.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 00:10:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/how-lungs-balance-defense-and-damage-by-tuning-responses-to-deeper-threats</guid></item><item><title>大多数在轨道上呆了六个月以上的宇航员回家后都会描述他们看待地球的方式发生了同样的变化，甚至那些提前了解情况的宇航员也表示，实际的感觉让他们措手不及</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/most-astronauts-who-spend-more-than-six-months-in-orbit-come-home-describing-the-same-shift-in-how-they-see-earth-and-even-the-ones-who-were-briefed-on-it-in-advance-say-the-actual-feeling-c</link><description>这种现象有一个名字。作家兼太空哲学家弗兰克·怀特在思考人们从太空观看地球作为日常生活的一部分意味着什么后，创造了“概览效应”一词。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/most-astronauts-who-spend-more-than-six-months-in-orbit-come-home-describing-the-same-shift-in-how-they-see-earth-and-even-the-ones-who-were-briefed-on-it-in-advance-say-the-actual-feeling-c.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2026 23:55:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/most-astronauts-who-spend-more-than-six-months-in-orbit-come-home-describing-the-same-shift-in-how-they-see-earth-and-even-the-ones-who-were-briefed-on-it-in-advance-say-the-actual-feeling-c</guid></item><item><title>有神论世界中的人类心灵</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/human-mind-in-a-theistic-world</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2026 23:40:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/human-mind-in-a-theistic-world</guid></item></channel></rss>